**Segments**

- On the basis of product type, the deflectable catheters market can be segmented into steerable catheters and non-steerable catheters. Steerable catheters are expected to dominate the market due to their ability to navigate complex anatomical structures with precision.

- Based on application, the market can be categorized into cardiology, urology, neurology, gastroenterology, and others. The cardiology segment is projected to hold a significant share of the market, driven by the increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases worldwide.

- By end-user, the deflectable catheters market can be divided into hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, specialty clinics, and others. Hospitals are anticipated to be the leading end-user segment, owing to the high volume of minimally invasive procedures performed in hospital settings.

